version_description: This tab includes extra instructions such as strumming, and includes the intro parts as well as the chords for the entire song. Essentially it is more complete than the tab already posted.
Chords played here https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Tni74ocFxtQ (mostly piano, but it works on guitar as well).
Includes chords, suggested fingerings, and keyboard melody.

This is a capo 2 version that represents the studio version in that, the second string is the highest sounding string ringing out throughout the performance, not the first string (high E). Play versions of chords that do not include the high E to keep it at that "rock ballad" style rather than poppy sounding which will occur if you play full D/G/A/Bm chords with high E included. Chord chart above will not be accurate but not sure how to their stock chord charts yet..
